  "data": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p id=\"docs-internal-guid-1032c89c-7fff-b66d-7849-2fa170ad2707\" style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">This long strip of leather was made for a sword but that can be attached to most weapons. With a command word, the grip magically seals to the wielder’s hand, preventing the weapon from being dropped by any means until the command word is spoken again. When found, these items are often still magically sealed to a hand or gauntlet, its last wielder unable to speak the command word to release the weapon before breathing their last.</span></p>\n<p style=\"line-height:1.38;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:12pt\"><span style=\"font-size:12pt;font-family:Arial;font-style:italic;font-variant-numeric:normal;font-variant-east-asian:normal;vertical-align:baseline;white-space:pre-wrap\">The dragon dangles the skeletal arm by the elbow, the sword still attached firmly to the long-dead adventurer’s hand. “He said he couldn’t be disarmed,” the dragon explains with a chuckle.</span></p>",
